The Ministry of Niger Delta Affairs is set to begin the training of various levels of its staff on areas to enhance staff capacity and delivery of functions. The Permanent Secretary at the Ministry, Olufunso Adebiyi on Monday disclosed that the in-house training which began July 18, with officials in the Directorate Cadre, will continue with officers on grade levels 14 and 15 respectively. He explained that the training would be of immense benefit to the participants as their performance capacity would be enhanced, he enjoined participants to take the training very seriously, adding, “You can’t be victorious and fall behind your mates, it is not possible.” The exercise which is been conducted by training officers from the Head of Civil Service of the Federation (HoCSF) covers such areas as, Performance Management System, Memo Writing, Public Service Procedures, Procurement Act, Financial Regulation and the New Reforms on Federal Civil Service Strategy Implementation Plan (FCSSIP) 2021 -2023.